<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHABARUM WON'T RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
County supervisors claim they can't afford to build roads or parks, but are 
going to be spending more than $5 million to defend a plan to keep themselves 
in office at the expense of Latinos and other county residents ("Latinos Urge 
Board to Settle Remap Suit With New District," Part B, March 14). When will the 
voters realize that their five elected representatives don't belong in office, 
they belong in jail. 
</P>
<P>
JIM JAMES 
</P>
<P>
Castaic 
</P>
