<P>
Signed into law a bill (SB 1372) by Sen. Nicholas Petris (D-Oakland) to require 
the use of automobile safety seat belts for all children under age 4 in all 
automobiles, including rental cars. 
</P>
<P>
Assembly 
</P>
<P>
Floor Action: 
</P>
<P>
Hate Crimes: Passed and sent to the Senate on a 41-20 vote a bill (AB 2683) by 
Assemblyman Richard Floyd (D-Carson) to allow victims of alleged hate violence 
to sue for monetary damages from public and private groups that violate their 
constitutional rights. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Introductions: 
</P>
<P>
