VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
THIEVES STAB MAN, TAKE HIS GROCERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard man who was stabbed in front of a market by two men who took his two 
bags of groceries was in fair condition Tuesday at St. John's Regional Medical 
Center, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Rafael Martinez Archila, 22, was leaving a grocery store in the 2800 block of 
Saviers Road when two Latino men approached him, Oxnard police Lt. Stan Myers 
said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the men demanded money. When Archila told him that he did not have any, 
the man grabbed him, a fight ensued and Archila was stabbed in the abdomen, 
Myers said. 
</P>
<P>
The men took Archila's bags of groceries, worth about $25, and drove away in a 
brown Chevrolet Impala, Myers said. 
</P>
<P>
Police described one assailant as a 30-year-old man with a heavy build and 
about 5 feet, 9 inches tall. The second suspect was described as about 22 years 
old and 5 feet, 9 inches tall, Myers said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
