<P>
A judge refused Tuesday to lower bail for Ernest Booker Brown, a Knox 
Elementary School teacher charged with 30 sex crimes against two female 
students. 
</P>
<P>
Brown, 47, remains in County Jail in lieu of $300,000 bail, after Superior 
Court Judge Jesus Rodriguez said the bail amount was appropriate. 
</P>
<P>
Brown is to go on trial June 15 on charges of molesting the girls, both 12, who 
testified against him in a closed preliminary hearing last month. 
</P>
<P>
His attorney, Alex Landon, cited Brown's ties to the community in arguing for a 
bail of $25,000. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Aaron Katz, noting that he had filed two additional child 
molestation counts against Brown on Tuesday, unsuccessfully asked that bail be 
raised to $400,000. 
</P>
<P>
"The defendant is facing 70 years if convicted," Katz said. 
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor said Brown had a child molestation conviction in Florida in 1977 
when he was a teacher there. 
</P>
<P>
Brown was arrested Nov. 30 at the Southeast San Diego school where he was 
teaching fourth- and fifth-graders. 
</P>
