MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mac's Back: Fleetwood Mac's first album of new material in three years, "Behind 
the Mask," will be out April 10 from Warner Bros. The band is now on tour in 
Australia; a U.S. tour is set for May. Current band members include Mick 
Fleetwood, Billy Burnette, Christine McVie, John McVie, Stevie Nicks and Rick 
Vito. BETH KLEID 
