<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Protest at Argentine Oscar Site: About 200 Argentine film industry workers, 
protesting against tax exemptions for foreign films, staged a noisy 
demonstration outside a theater in Buenos Aires where winners of two Hollywood 
Oscars were announced early Tuesday. While Charlton Heston and Argentine 
actress Norma Aleandro read out the winners of the best documentary categories, 
outside the Colon Theatre film workers handed out leaflets which read: "Oscar 
pays no taxes. Today television shows a black-tie Argentina to the world, 
hiding the reality of a devastated industry, with thousands of unemployed 
artists and technicians." BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
