<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP PLAYER STRIKES OUT 20 IN 7 INNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryan McGuire, a senior left-hander from Woodland Hills El Camino Real High, 
struck out 20 batters in a regulation, seven-inning baseball game Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
McGuire, a 6-foot-2 left-hander, threw a five-hitter, walked one and allowed 
one earned run as El Camino Real defeated Reseda Cleveland, 7-2. McGuire, who 
struck out 18 in a nine-inning game in his most recent start last Tuesday, 
retired the first batter on a ground ball to second before getting the next 20 
outs on strikes. 
</P>
<P>
The state record for a seven-inning game was set in 1973 by Jim Peterson of La 
Habra Sonora. Peterson struck out 22, with one batter reaching base on a passed 
ball by the catcher. 
</P>
