</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chet Brewer, 83, of Los Angeles, a Negro Leagues pitcher who has been compared 
to Satchel Paige, died at Presbyterian Intercommunity Hospital in Whittier of 
complications after surgery. 
</P>
<P>
Brewer played professional baseball for 28 years, beginning in 1925, mainly 
with the Kansas City Monarchs. 
</P>
<P>
After his playing career, he started a semi-pro team in Central Los Angeles 
that produced such major league stars as Bobby Tolan, Dock Ellis and Willie 
Crawford. 
</P>
<P>
Brewer is survived by his wife, Tina, and son, Chester Eugene. 
</P>
<P>
Funeral arrangements are pending. 
</P>
