<P>
Citicorp Passes American Express: Citicorp had issued 35 million MasterCard, 
Visa and Diners Club cards, according to year-end data published by the 
companies. While Citicorp has long led U.S. banks in MasterCard and Visa 
issuance, it now lays claim to an international leadership position, with cards 
a linchpin of its global consumer banking strategy. American Express Travel 
Related Services Co. said it had issued 34 million green, gold, platinum and 
Optima cards worldwide at the end of 1989. 
