<P>
CROWN CORK &amp; SEAL TO BUY CANNING UNITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crown Cork &amp; Seal Co. has agreed to buy the food and beverage metal canning 
units of Continental Can Co. in a purchase that will make Crown the nation's 
largest maker of metal packaging. 
</P>
<P>
Crown, based in Philadelphia, said it would pay $336 million for the two 
divisions, which have more than 30 U.S. plants and employ 4,000 workers. 
