CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
EL TORO DOCTOR HAS LICENSE REVOKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State medical officials said they have revoked the license of an El Toro 
physician accused of administering a hormonal treatment that posed a public 
danger and caused harmful side-effects in at least 18 women. Dr. Norman King 
Beals Jr., 55, who hosted a call-in radio talk show in Orange County and 
advertised heavily in local newspapers, admitted that the California Medical 
Board's allegations were true and declined to contest the charges at an 
evidentiary hearing, according to documents filed last week by the state 
attorney general's office. Beals had touted "hormonal replacement therapy" as a 
cure-all for a host of female-oriented afflictions -- including breast cancer, 
menopausal hot flashes and premenstrual syndrome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
