<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: KOREAN CULTURAL SERVICE TO MARK 10TH 
ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Korean Cultural Service, in the Park La Brea neighborhood, will celebrate 
its 10th anniversary April 11 beginning at 6 p.m. with an art exhibit and an 
experimental music performance. 
</P>
<P>
The exhibit, entitled "East Bound, West Bound," features nine artists from 
Korea and the United States. The concert, "No World Improvisation," will be 
performed on the oboe and traditional komungo, a six-stringed board zither. 
</P>
<P>
The Korean Cultural Service provides Los Angeles with opportunities to see 
Korea through its art and literary works and has arranged exchange programs 
between museums, universities and galleries around the world. 
</P>
<P>
The Cultural Service is at 5505 Wilshire Blvd. at Dunsmuir Avenue. Information 
is available at (213) 936-7141. 
</P>
</TEXT>
