<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FERRARO SEES LIKELIHOOD OF WATER RATIONING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Council President John Ferraro on Tuesday said "there is a strong 
possibility" that Los Angeles will resort to water rationing this summer in the 
face of a projected 12% shortfall in water supplies. 
</P>
<P>
But Ferraro, following a council committee hearing on the Department of Water 
and Power's projections, said he does not believe that strict enforcement 
methods are necessary or cost-effective in saving water. 
</P>
<P>
"The people have responded in the past and they will again" answer the call to 
reduce water usage and honor rationing levels, Ferraro said. "We can't expect 
the police . . . to check on every leaky water faucet," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
