<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PINNACLE: During the post-Watergate years, former President Richard M. Nixon 
writes in this week's Time, golf was his "lifesaver." 
</P>
<P>
.. . But he abruptly quit the game after breaking 80 on a relatively easy San 
Clemente golf course. "For me," he writes, "it was like climbing Mount Everest. 
I knew I could never get better." . . . Nixon returns to Orange County on July 
19 for the opening ceremonies of his presidential library in Yorba Linda. Mark 
I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
