<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
DIVINE SPIRIT SEEKING 4TH STRAIGHT WIN IN CALIF. SIRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Divine Spirit will be looking for her fourth straight win when she tackles 
Goodness Gracie and seven others in the $20,000 California Sires Stakes for 
sophomore trotting fillies Thursday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
It is the final sires stakes battle of the Los Alamitos winter-spring session 
for sophomore fillies. 
</P>
<P>
First post will be at 7:30 p.m. The feature is the eighth race. 
</P>
<P>
The field, in post position order: Divine Spirit, Rick Plano in the race bike; 
Congressional Star, Fritz Haug; Goodness Gracie, Jim Grundy; Gemstar Anna, Ross 
Croghan; How High The Moon, Nicol Tremblay; Magna Ms., Gaetan Brunet; Typical 
Anna, Rick Kuebler; Kimmie's April, Steve Desomer, and Lovely Lorraine, Tim 
Maier. 
</P>
<P>
Divine Spirit has scored five times this year from seven starts and has earned 
more than $63,000 lifetime. She beat Kimmie's April and Goodness Gracie in a 
similar breeders' stakes on March 8. 
</P>
<P>
She seems to get better with each race and is considered as the one to beat; 
Goodness Gracie, Typical Anna and Kimmie's April all have a chance to provide 
an upset. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
